description.p: The Process Owner and/or SME will either provide feedback or approval of the PDD. Once all feedback is implemented the approval will be given through an email which will be logged into the PDD for future reference.

ul.li: PDD Quality Check - internal check to ensure consistency in quality standards
PDD Review Session with Process SME/Owner
PDD Approval from Process SME and Owner
Any updates needed will have to be completed within one business day to avoid delays
Any disagreements will be brought up to the POD Lead
The PDD QA Checklist is meant to remain flexible, feel free to provide feedback as needed
Only when the approval is given the SDLC process can continue
Ensure the To-Be process map and exception list is thoroughly reviewed
If possible, the review session is to be held in person to ensure full attention is given
If proper attention is not given by the Process Owner and/or SME it needs to be escalated to the RPA CoE
Any changes resulting from the review session will need to be implemented within 2 business days
The Process Owner/SME can take an additional 2 days to review the PDD on their own and run a transaction through the process to ensure all steps have been taken in account
Any delays in approving the PDD need to be escalated and logged in the project plan
Some sections of the PDD might remain pending, but the Process Map, process steps and exceptions cannot
The approval needs to be given through email, no verbal approvals will be accepted
The approval email will be stored within the PDD and shared accordingly with the RPA CoE
